(Molina) to 1) charge the total balance due on My Molina account the day I signed up and 2) starting in the following month, charge an automatic payment of the current balance owed (please check your invoice for amount) on the 23rd of each month or the next banking day as long as my coverage with Molina Healthcare Inc. remains in effect. 

I understand that if I am paying by credit or debit card, I will be charged the current balance owed each month on my Credit/Debit card or if I am paying via auto-debit from my bank account, my Checking or Savings account will be charged the balance owed each month. Adjustments to my premium amount may be necessary when I make changes to my account regarding my income, my family size, or my residence address. Molina is authorized to make adjustments to the amount Molina charges to my Credit/Debit card or my bank account when a correction or change is required. For example, if Molina makes an error, I agree that Molina may correct the error immediately and without notice to me. Such errors may include, but are not limited to, reversing an improper credit, making adjustments for returned premium, and correcting calculation and input errors. Molina may make the adjustments as necessary and the amounts of such adjustments and the corresponding amount Molina may charge to my Credit / Debit card or bank account is not subject to any limitations or time constraints, except as required by law. I understand that Molina will notify me on my monthly invoice of each such adjustment.

I authorize Molina Healthcare, Inc. (Molina) to 1) charge the total balance due on My Molina account the day I signed up and 2) starting in the following month, charge an automatic payment of the current balance owed (please check your invoice for amount) on the 23rd of each month or the next banking day as long as my coverage with Molina Healthcare Inc. remains in effect. I understand that if I am paying by credit or debit card, I will be charged the current balance owed each month on my Credit/Debit card or if I am paying via auto-debit from my bank account, my Checking or Savings account will be charged the balance owed each month. Adjustments to my premium amount may be necessary when I make changes to my account regarding my income, my family size, or my residence address. Molina is authorized to make adjustments to the amount Molina charges to my Credit/Debit card or my bank account when a correction or change is required. For example, if Molina makes an error, I agree that Molina may correct the error immediately and without notice to me. Such errors may include, but are not limited to, reversing an improper credit, making adjustments for returned premium, and correcting calculation and input errors. Molina may make the adjustments as necessary and the amounts of such adjustments and the corresponding amount Molina may charge to my Credit / Debit card or bank account is not subject to any limitations or time constraints, except as required by law. I understand that Molina will notify me on my monthly invoice of each such adjustment.

I understand that this authorization will remain in effect until it is canceled. To cancel AutoPay, I will sign in to My Molina account and select “Manage Accounts” where I can disable AutoPay. If I have never accessed My Molina account, I will need to register first. If I need to make changes to my account information, I will do so through My Molina account. If the above specified payment dates fall on a weekend or holiday, I understand that the payments may be executed on the next banking day. I certify to Molina that I am an authorized user of the credit card provided in this authorization and I will not dispute the payments with my credit card company so long as the transactions are made as authorized pursuant to this authorization.
I understand that:

Payment will be withdrawn on the 23rd of each month. If the 23rd falls on a weekend or bank holiday, withdrawal will be moved to the next banking day.

I am authorizing a one-time payment of the balance due as well as authorizing the automatic premium payments, which will be charged to my Credit /Debit card or bank account the following month.

If my bank account does not have enough funds, Molina may (but is not required to) try again in the next three banking days. If Molina is still unable to receive the premium, the premium will be considered not paid.

If payment can’t be made, this may result in the cancellation/ termination of my insurance coverage.

If the first month’s payment was made prior to the beginning of the coverage year then the automatic payment will start with the first month of the coverage year. Example – For coverage beginning on January 1st, your automatic payment will start on January 23rd to pay February’s premium.

If the payment amount changes, Molina will notify you on your monthly invoice at least ten days before the payment will be charged to your Credit / Debit card or bank account.

To make changes or to disable your AutoPay account, go to MyMolina.com and select the Manage Accounts tab."

SYNOPSIS
 java org.apache.xalan.xsltc.cmdline.Compile [-o <выходной-файл>]
 [-d <каталог>] [-j <файл-jar>] [-p <пакет>]
 [-n] [-x] [-u] [-v] [-h] { <таблица-стилей> | -i }

ОПЦИИ
 -o <выходной-файл> присваивает имя <выходной-файл> созданному объекту 
 translet. По умолчанию имя процедуры преобразования
            берется из имени <таблицы-стилей>. При компиляции нескольких таблиц стилей
                  эта опция игнорируется.
   -d <каталог> задает целевой каталог для процедуры преобразования
   -j <файл-jar> упаковывает классы процедуры преобразования 
                  в <файл-jar> с указанным именем
   -p <пакет>   задает префикс имени пакета для всех созданных
                  классов процедуры преобразования
   -n             разрешает копирование строк шаблона (обычно способ, применяемый по умолчанию,
 работает лучше).
   -x выдавать подробные отладочные сообщения 
 -u интерпретировать аргументы <таблицы-стилей> как URL
 -i читать таблицу стилей из stdin
 -v показать версию компилятора
 -h выдать это сообщение

na média).

  -u interpreta argumentos <stylesheet> como URLs

   -x             attiva ulteriori emissioni dei messaggi di debug
   -u             interpreta gli argomenti <stylesheet> come URL
   -i             impone al programma di compilazione di leggere il foglio di lavoro da stdin
   -v             stampa la versione del programma di compilazione

                  on average).
   -x             turns on additional debugging message output

playstore_details.description:
Members can sign into the app using their My Molina User ID and Password to access our secure features, including:

• User friendly navigation
• View health coverage
• View your benefits and eligibility
• View/download and share ID card
• Make premium payments (Marketplace only)
• Manage your payment profile
• Save favorite doctors
• Change PCP
• Access to other services

When you use the My Molina app, identifiers for your mobile device are collected within Google Firebase to create a unique identifier for each application when downloaded. 
Please review the below link which provides a disclosure of the use of Google Analytics for Firebase and how that service processes data: www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/

high.title: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
high.description:
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.

hotspot.title: Found 12 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION (dangerous): fine (GPS) location - Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read external storage contents - Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.CAMERA (dangerous): take pictures and videos - Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (dangerous): allows reading image files from external storage. - Allows an application to read image files from external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_VIDEO (dangerous): allows reading video files from external storage. - Allows an application to read video files from external storage.

android.permission.READ_MEDIA_AUDIO (dangerous): allows reading audio files from external storage. - Allows an application to read audio files from external storage.

android.permission.READ_LOGS (dangerous): read sensitive log data - Allows an application to read from the system's various log files. This allows it to discover general information about what you are doing with the phone, potentially including personal or private information.

android.permission.CALL_PHONE (dangerous): directly call phone numbers - Allows the application to call phone numbers without your intervention. Malicious applications may cause unexpected calls on your phone bill. Note that this does not allow the application to call emergency numbers.

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW (dangerous): display system-level alerts - Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.
